Enter the Hobo Restaurant. Its an excuse to stop for a bite to eat rather than get out of your scooting gear and trying to zip up everything in plastic bags from the store if you don't have a car. And, let me tell you, Hobo is worth the 500m scooter ride of pure calorie burning insanity. With a wide array of food things and stuff Hobo is known for its Macaroni pies! Well, I thought I would have an eggs Benedict, you know, drive up to the restaurant and have the car easily search for parking (after my scooter workout). But, I couldn't resist the fabulous scent of the macaroni pie.

So this was a full 11:30am breakfast of beef stew, 3 eggs, onions, celery, tomatoes, olives, fresh greens, and pieces of potato. Chase-N-Angel made it that far. I could only manage 1/2.

But, its one of those around the World breakfasts that you must try if you are in Malta. It was not only brown but creamy with a thick meaty gravy and oodles of butter potato, egg, and celery. With the veggies there was fresh greens with a zing of lemon or dressing. I had honey and
